304
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,593
Mr. Markowitz? You have a visitor.

305
00:16:08,594 --> 00:16:10,345
Oh. I do?

306
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:16,050
- [SIGHS] Thanks, man.
- You're welcome.

307
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,812
Good afternoon, sir.

308
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:22,900
My friends and I are
reading to seniors today.

309
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,194
Would... Would you
like me to read to you?

310
00:16:30,115 --> 00:16:32,868
"I seen it over and over.

311
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:36,997
A guy talkin' to another guy
and it don't make no difference

312
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:40,876
if he don't hear or understand.

313
00:16:40,959 --> 00:16:45,630
The thing is, they're talkin' or
they're settling still not talking.

314
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:48,217
It's just bein' with
another guy." [SIGHS]

315
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:50,135
Why are you here, Terrel?

316
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:54,640
You don't actually care
about me, do you?

317
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:01,000
No. You... You're okay. You're cool.

318
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,040
[SCOFFS]

319
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:03,700
- I'm cool?
- [TERREL] Yeah.

320
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:04,816
No.

321
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,560
I'm not cool.

322
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,520
Why are you really here?

323
00:17:09,780 --> 00:17:11,150
[SIGHS]

324
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:14,409
Honestly, I just need some
stuff to put on my college app.

325
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:18,160
It was either this or band,
and I hate band, so...

326
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,915
Oh, everyone hates band.

327
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:27,256
Well, at least you're honest.

328
00:17:27,339 --> 00:17:28,549
Don't ever lose that.

329
00:17:32,135 --> 00:17:33,345
Uh, so...

330
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,590
do you want me to keep
reading, sir, or...

331
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,970
You know what? Um, yeah. Why not?

332
00:17:41,061 --> 00:17:42,271
Thanks, Terrel.

333
00:17:44,100 --> 00:17:45,270
Uh... [SIGHS]

334
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:48,770
"Sure, you could play
horseshoes till it got dark,

335
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,860
but then you got to read books.

336
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,197
Books ain't no good.

337
00:17:52,948 --> 00:17:55,784
A guy needs somebody to be near him.

338
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:58,410
A guy goes nuts if he ain't got nobody.

339
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:02,830
Don't make no difference who the
guy is, long as he's with you.

340
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:07,160
I tell ya, a guy gets too
lonely an' he gets sick."

341
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,922
You can stop there, Terrel.

342
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,340
Thank you.

343
00:18:23,353 --> 00:18:25,856
[STRAINS, GRUNTS]

344
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:36,283
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, LAUGHING]

345
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,450
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

346
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:46,710
Mr. Markowitz?

347
00:18:48,180 --> 00:18:49,540
Mr. Markowitz.

348
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,000
You can't leave.

349
00:18:52,090 --> 00:18:54,468
- Come back here. Sir.
- [ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

350
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:56,220
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

351
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:02,140
What do you think you're
doing? Mr. Markowitz!

352
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,100
[SIGHS] Fuck.

353
00:19:06,188 --> 00:19:07,189
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

354
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,900
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

355
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:33,173
[LOUD MUSIC PLAYING]

356
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,980
Everybody, duck!

357
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,810
- Don't say it. Don't even think it.
- [CHUCKLES] What?

358
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:55,320
- I'm not playing golf with you again.
- Why not?

359
00:19:55,350 --> 00:19:57,905
"Why not?" That wasn't golf.
That was more like hockey.

360
00:19:57,906 --> 00:19:59,324
I was afraid for my life.

361
00:19:59,408 --> 00:20:01,994
[IKE] Have you tried the hot tub
yet? You should try the hot tub.

362
00:20:02,380 --> 00:20:04,980
- Even you can't miss that.
- [RICHARD] Ooh, I ought to...

363
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:09,060
[IKE] Have you seen the sundial?

364
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:11,044
- [WOMAN] No.
- No? No? Here, look.

365
00:20:11,753 --> 00:20:13,380
Thirty-six feet tall.

366
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,780
And you know, to get it in,
I had to chop down a tree

367
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,340
and install it by crane.

368
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,051
- Amazing.
- Yeah?

369
00:20:19,052 --> 00:20:21,346
- [IKE] Do you know what time it is?
- [WOMAN] No.

370
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,140
[IKE] Cocktail time.

371
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,807
You don't need a sundial
to tell you that.

372
00:20:24,808 --> 00:20:27,644
- [LAUGHS] No, you don't.
- [CHUCKLES]

373
00:20:27,728 --> 00:20:29,479
You most certainly do not.

374
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:32,274
Um, have you played the giant chess?

375
00:20:32,357 --> 00:20:34,902
[STAMMERS] Go ahead and,
uh, play some giant chess.

376
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:40,579
Marty, my sweet. Why...
Why are you so dressed up?

377
00:20:40,580 --> 00:20:42,618
It's not a formal party. [CHUCKLES]

378
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,320
I need to talk to you.

379
00:20:44,990 --> 00:20:46,920
[STAMMERS] Oh, yeah. Sure, of course.

380
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:48,999
Hey, come on. [STAMMERS] Let's...

381
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,790
Oh, Marty, your... your
tush is hanging out.

382
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,630
Here. Here. Okay.

383
00:20:57,716 --> 00:21:00,219
- All right.
- Who's that?

384
00:21:00,302 --> 00:21:04,097
Oh, that's, uh, Chef Pete.
I hired him for the party.

385
00:21:04,181 --> 00:21:06,933
He used to cook for Kevin
Bacon and Kyra Sedgwick.

386
00:21:06,934 --> 00:21:09,061
He's good, but he's no Marty Markowitz.

387
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,230
All right.

388
00:21:12,272 --> 00:21:13,356
What's going on?

389
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:18,770
For the better part of
the last three decades...

390
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:23,650
I have dedicated my life to you.

391
00:21:23,742 --> 00:21:26,870
Every weekend, every
holiday, everything.

392
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:30,780
And you couldn't even
find time in your schedule

393
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,790
over the course of four days
to come... come visit me?

394
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:35,500
To call me?

395
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,060
To check in on me

396
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:40,420
during one of the most harrowing
experiences of my life?

397
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:44,749
Okay, I know they pumped
you full of narcotics, Marty,

398
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:47,306
and that you're a lightweight, so
I'm assuming it's hitting you hard.

399
00:21:47,307 --> 00:21:49,769
I don't underst... You wanted me
to, what, come by the hospital

400
00:21:49,770 --> 00:21:52,120
with Jell-O and ice
cream, uh, snuggle up

401
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:53,897
- and watch <i>Jungle Book</i>?
- Why?

402
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,440
Why didn't you come?

403
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,735
I thought we were family.

404
00:21:59,740 --> 00:22:01,080
[SCOFFS]

405
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:03,190
Are you serious?

406
00:22:03,282 --> 00:22:05,533
Marty, I'm worried that you're serious.

407
00:22:06,076 --> 00:22:08,245
You need to know this.
You need to hear this.

408
00:22:08,270 --> 00:22:11,664
I would do anything for you. Anything.

409
00:22:11,665 --> 00:22:13,876
The second you told me
about your procedure,

410
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:17,230
I called my contacts at NYU
Langone the very next day.

411
00:22:17,254 --> 00:22:18,671
I told them that we're family.

412
00:22:18,672 --> 00:22:21,425
The hospital bed, the
private room you had.

413
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:23,510
Who do you think did that? I did that.

414
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:29,760
I can't believe you didn't think
I would do anything. Wh...

415
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:32,728
After all these years,
is that how you see me?

416
00:22:32,811 --> 00:22:35,813
[STAMMERS] I was just surprised
that you didn't come and visit.

417
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:39,460
Why didn't you ask me to come? I...

418
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:41,019
Do you think I'm that much of a schmuck?

419
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:43,419
You don't think I'm gonna come and...
Of course. Why didn't you say,

420
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:46,213
"Ike, it would mean a
lot if you swung by"?

421
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:47,618
I'm not a mind reader.

422
00:22:47,630 --> 00:22:49,995
- Well, why...
- You say that you've been by my side

423
00:22:50,010 --> 00:22:51,489
for the better part of three decades.

424
00:22:51,490 --> 00:22:53,331
Well, I'd argue the same thing.

425
00:22:53,332 --> 00:22:55,890
When Debbie and your
sister tried to bleed you dry

426
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:57,211
after your parents died,

427
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:58,544
who was there, hmm?

428
00:22:58,545 --> 00:23:00,850
What about when AFC wanted
to grow and expand?

429
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,591
Who provided you with that opportunity?

430
00:23:02,620 --> 00:23:04,220
When you had a heart attack,

431
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:08,347
who scooped you up and held
your hand in the ambulance?

432
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:11,220
Who saved your life?

433
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:15,770
Marty...

434
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:19,357
That's loyalty.

435
00:23:20,060 --> 00:23:21,690
That's love.

436
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:24,612
I'd do anything for you. You're my guy.

437
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:27,282
I will always show up for you.

438
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:31,870
You're absolutely right.

439
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:33,140
[SOBS]

440
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:34,538
I'm sorry.

441
00:23:34,550 --> 00:23:36,834
- I'm... I'm... I'm sorry.
- Come here, you maniac.

442
00:23:36,850 --> 00:23:38,877
Come... [CHUCKLES] Come...

443
00:23:38,970 --> 00:23:43,340
Oh. Marty, I love you.
You are my brother.

444
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:46,840
- You hear me?
- Mm-hmm.

445
00:23:46,860 --> 00:23:48,260
- Are you listening?
- Yeah.

446
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:49,930
Good.

447
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:54,266
Now get out of this farkakte outfit
and meet me by the pool, huh?

448
00:23:54,270 --> 00:23:55,780
- All right. All right.
- [KISSES]

449
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:57,430
- [SIGHS]
- Okay.

450
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:01,441
Money in the bank. Ready? Jump.

451
00:24:01,470 --> 00:24:04,653
- He's hot. Oh!
- [MAN LAUGHS]

452
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:07,140
You just made a hundred bucks.

453
00:24:14,036 --> 00:24:17,498
[IKE] ... because your mother
raised you as veal. [CHUCKLES]

454
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,579
Let's go in here, all right?
There's air-conditioning.

455
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:21,962
There are hundreds of movies,
all Academy Award winners.

456
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,630
- [GRUNTS]
- Mind the boccie balls.

457
00:24:26,260 --> 00:24:27,717
- Hi, tchotchke.
- Hi.

458
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:29,178
Having a good time? [KISSES]

459
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:31,013
- Uh-huh.
- Oh, great.

460
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:33,389
Uh, maybe you could send
the message to your face?

461
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,474
What?

462
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:36,476
Maybe you can arrange your features

463
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:39,854
in a configuration that expresses
some form of enjoyment.

464
00:24:39,860 --> 00:24:41,820
- Oh, fuck you, Ike.
- Come on. [SCOFFS, CHUCKLES]

465
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:44,026
I'm kidding. I'm kid...
You look terrific.

466
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:46,278
I'm worried. What is
going on with Marty?

467
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:47,696
What? Nothing. He's fine.

468
00:24:48,100 --> 00:24:50,520
Yeah, well, he's a little loopy
post-surgery, but he's fine.

469
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:52,400
[BONNIE] No, he doesn't seem fine.

470
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:55,245
Maybe we should just wrap this
up and just get him some rest.

471
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:58,582
Wrap this up? What, are you
crazy? Lisa Rinna just got here.

472
00:24:58,670 --> 00:25:00,209
Should we bring him something to eat?

473
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,929
Yeah, sure. I don't know.
If you think so.

474
00:25:01,930 --> 00:25:03,504
But one of us has to host this party.

475
00:25:03,530 --> 00:25:04,940
I know, but I... I don't know.

476
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:06,589
I think we should just shut this down

477
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,175
and send everybody home. He's not okay.

478
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:09,593
What are you, the fun police?

479
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:12,520
[STAMMERS] Well, um, don't be
ridiculous, Bonnie. All right?

480
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:15,149
I've already got one ridiculous wife.
His name is Marty Markowitz.

481
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:16,760
You don't have to tell me that.

482
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:20,680
[CLICKS TONGUE]

483
00:25:27,140 --> 00:25:29,737
[MARTY] Stu, get away from that rock.

484
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:31,949
You always get caught in
that little roundabout.

485
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,000
[SIGHS]

486
00:25:35,020 --> 00:25:36,828
So, did you guys miss me?

487
00:25:38,820 --> 00:25:41,160
